  "text": "In euvolemic surgical patients, almost all randomized studies to date have shown that the use of a \"restrictive\" transfusion threshold does not cause an increase in mortality or morbidity or in the duration of the hospital stay, while reducing both the percentage of patients transfused and the volume of allogeneic blood administered 42-48. The exception is from the work of Foss et al., but it was not designed to evaluate this objective and it lacked the statistical power to evaluate it [CITATION_1] .",
